(53, 1, '2011-04-02 03:40:55', '2011-04-02 03:40:55', 'Grand Auditorium, Conservatoire de Luxembourg\r\n\r\nAfter : read more on a)Events and b) News\r\n\r\nEnsemble M&M was founded in 2008. Ever since the double father and son duo- Jean and Gary Muller, Michel and Paul Mootz - has experienced growing success. In 2010 they engaged in the production of DVD that will be presented to the Luxembourgish public at a concert in the Conservatoire de Luxembourg on March 27, 2011. The program includes works by Gershwin, Bernstein, Rachmaninov and as a special highlight the world premiere of an arrangement of John Williams’ "Star Wars Suite" by John Williams, arranged by Jan Valta.\r\n\r\n', 'Chopin CD Release Concert, JEAN MULLER Piano Recital', 'Grand Auditorium, Conservatoire de LuxembourgDVD', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-revision-7', '', '', '2011-04-02 03:40:55', '2011-04-02 03:40:55', '', 43, 'http://www.musicandmore.lu/wp/?p=53', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(54, 1, '2011-04-02 04:08:15', '2011-04-02 04:08:15', 'The young Austrian violinist Martha Khadem-Missagh, born in November 1979, started playing the violin at the age of three, gave her first public performance with five and debut as soloist with orchestra at the age of nine.\r\n \r\n    She continues the musical tradition in the fourth generation. She received first violin lessons from her father and Margarete Biedermann. She studied with Eugenia Polatschek at the Conservatory of Music Vienna, and at the Academy of Music and Performing Arts Vienna with Gerhard Schulz (Alban Berg Quartet) and Christian Altenburger. Masterclasses with Robert McDuffie, Rainer Kussmaul, Krzysztof Wegrzyn.\r\n \r\n   Concerts throughout Europe, USA, South ', 'Martha Khadem-Missagh', 'Austria', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'martha-khadem-missagh', '', '', '2011-04-02 04:10:23', '2011-04-02 04:10:23', '', 0, 'http://www.musicandmore.lu/wp/?p=54', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(55, 1, '2011-04-02 04:07:41', '2011-04-02 04:07:41', 'The young Austrian violinist Martha Khadem-Missagh, born in November 1979, started playing the violin at the age of three, gave her first public performance with five and debut as soloist with orchestra at the age of nine.\n \n    She continues the musical tradition in the fourth generation. She received first violin lessons from her father and Margarete Biedermann. She studied with Eugenia Polatschek at the Conservatory of Music Vienna, and at the Academy of Music and Performing Arts Vienna with Gerhard Schulz (Alban Berg Quartet) and Christian Altenburger. Masterclasses with Robert McDuffie, Rainer Kussmaul, Krzysztof Wegrzyn.\n \n   Concerts throughout Europe, USA, South ', 'Martha Khadem-Missagh', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '54-revision', '', '', '2011-04-02 04:07:41', '2011-04-02 04:07:41', '', 54, 'http://www.musicandmore.lu/wp/?p=55', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(56, 1, '2011-04-02 04:08:15', '2011-04-02 04:08:15', 'The young Austrian violinist Martha Khadem-Missagh, born in November 1979, started playing the violin at the age of three, gave her first public performance with five and debut as soloist with orchestra at the age of nine.\r\n \r\n    She continues the musical tradition in the fourth generation. She received first violin lessons from her father and Margarete Biedermann. She studied with Eugenia Polatschek at the Conservatory of Music Vienna, and at the Academy of Music and Performing Arts Vienna with Gerhard Schulz (Alban Berg Quartet) and Christian Altenburger. Masterclasses with Robert McDuffie, Rainer Kussmaul, Krzysztof Wegrzyn.\r\n \r\n   Concerts throughout Europe, USA, South ', 'Martha Khadem-Missagh', 'Austria', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '54-revision-2', '', '', '2011-04-02 04:08:15', '2011-04-02 04:08:15', '', 54, 'http://www.musicandmore.lu/wp/?p=56', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(57, 1, '2011-04-01 15:57:39', '2011-04-01 15:57:39', 'Jean Muller was born in 1979. He attended his first piano lessons with Marie-José Hengesch at the Conservatory of Luxembourg at the age of six. Only one year later he gave his first public performance, creating a work of his compatriot Alexander Mullenbach. But it is only at the age of 15, when - as the result of his excellent studies - he was granted a scholarship to study one semester with professor Teofils Bikis at the Latvian state academy for music in Riga, that he decided to devote his life to music. Afterwards, he studied in Brussels, Paris and Munich with Evgeny Moguilevsky, Gerhard Oppitz, Eugen Indjic and Michael Schäfer. Besides his studies it was his father and mentor Gary Muller, professor for piano in Luxemburg, who had a major influence on his musical development. During master classes he has also been advised by such distinguished artists as Anne Queffélec, Leon Fleischer, Janos Starker, Fou Ts''ong...\r\n<img src="http://music/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/demo2.jpg" alt="" title="demo2" width="141" height="137" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-34" /><img src="http://music/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/demo2.jpg" alt="" title="demo2" width="141" height="137" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-34" /><img src="http://music/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/demo2.jpg" alt="" title="demo2" width="141" height="137" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-34" />', 'Music & More is proud to announce the DVD Release Concert of Ensemble M&M featuring Kae Shiraki on March 27 th at the Conservatoire de Luxembourg.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '24-revision-12', '', '', '2011-04-01 15:57:39', '2011-04-01 15:57:39', '', 24, 'http://www.musicandmore.lu/wp/?p=57', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
